3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW
3.2.1 鈥婼ESSION FIXATION CWE-384
鈥婣ffected devices do not renew the session cookie after login/logout and accept user defined session cookies. An attacker could overwrite the stored session cookie of a user. After the victim has logged in, the attacker is given access to the user's account through the activated session.
鈥婥VE-2022-43398 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.5 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).
3.2.2 鈥婭MPROPER INPUT VALIDATION CWE-20
鈥婣ffected devices do not properly validate the Language-parameter in requests to the web interface on port 443/tcp. This could allow an authenticated remote attacker to crash the device (followed by an automatic reboot) or to execute arbitrary code on the device.
鈥婥VE-2022-43439 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 9.9 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).
3.2.3 鈥婭MPROPER INPUT VALIDATION CWE-20
鈥婣ffected devices do not properly validate the RecordType-parameter in requests to the web interface on port 443/tcp. This could allow an authenticated remote attacker to crash the device (followed by an automatic reboot) or to execute arbitrary code on the device.
鈥婥VE-2022-43545 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 9.9 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).
3.2.4聽IMPROPER INPUT VALIDATION CWE-20
鈥婣ffected devices do not properly validate the EndTime-parameter in requests to the web interface on port 443/tcp. This could allow an authenticated remote attacker to crash the device (followed by an automatic reboot) or to execute arbitrary code on the device.
鈥婥VE-2022-43546 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 9.9 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).
3.2.5 鈥婥ROSS-SITE REQUEST FORGERY (CSRF) CWE-352
鈥婽he web interface of the affected devices is vulnerable to cross-site request forgery attacks. By tricking an authenticated victim user to click a malicious link, an attacker could perform arbitrary actions on the device on behalf of the victim user.
鈥婥VE-2023-30901 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 4.3 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N).
3.2.6 鈥婭NCORRECT PERMISSION ASSIGNMENT FOR CRITICAL RESOURCE CWE-732
鈥婣ffected devices are missing cookie protection flags when using the default settings. An attacker who gains access to a session token can use it to impersonate a legitimate application user.
鈥婥VE-2023-31238 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 5.5 has been calculated. The CVSS vector string is (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:L).
